<TITLE> Delwar meets with feuding Ctg leaders </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 18 (bdnews24.com)BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain held talks on Wednesday with senior leaders of the two feuding factions who battled over supremacy in Chittagong a couple of days ago. The meeting was held for four hours from 1pm. "The secretary general has summoned the Chittagong metropolitan BNP stalwarts," office secretary Rizvi Ahmed said to bdnews24.com before the meeting. Chittagong metropolitan BNP unit convenor Amir Khasru Mahmud Chowdhury, central committee vice president M Morshed Khan, party joint secretary general Abdullah Al Noman, central committee international affairs secretary Mir Mohammad Nasir Uddin, metropolitan convening committee joint convenor Wahidul Alam, Shamsul Alam and Shahadat Hossain have been called in. Wahidul Alam and Mir Mohammad Nasir Uddin arrived at the Naya Paltan office at 12 noon and said to bdnews24.com the secretary general has sent for them. Seven of them got invited on the occasion, they added. A series of clashes fuelled by internal squabbling foiled the Chittagong council, attempted after a hiatus of 20 years on Monday. Supporters of BNP joint secretary general Abdullah Al Noman and Amir Khasru blamed each other for the untoward occurrences at the Institution of Engineers, Chittagong, where the scheduled council dissolved in chaos as the two factions faced off. Following the clashes, BNP chief Khaleda Zia put Delwar in charge of resolving the matter through discussing the issues in presence of both parties. b
